<h3>wrong keyboard and time</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>I&#039;m new to Linux and Parrot Security OS was the choice for my first Linux distro.</p><p>I can install and boot the OS, but the keyboard and time settings are wrong. </p><p>I&#039;m German, and the notebook is a Lenovo Thinkpad E470 with a German QWERTZ keyboard. <br/>So I choose in the installation Language: German, Location: Germany, and Keyboard Layout: German, <br/>but after installing, the keyboard works as QWERTY and also some symbols are wrong. </p><p>The default time settings are also wrong and I can change them easily in the MATE menu, but after another login the time settings are the same wrong default settings.</p>
</div>
