<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: wrong keyboard and time</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Greetings,</p><p>I&#039;m not sure how much this will help, but ever since I started using Raspberry Pi, I just do the following three commands as soon as I boot in for the first time.</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
sudo dpkg-reconfigure keyboard-configuration</code></pre></div><p>I never had problems with time zone, locales and keyboard problem once going thru those three commands.&#160; I am informed correctly, those three commands should be pretty universal. =)&#160; If I&#039;m wrong, correction would be appreciated.</p><p>Peace.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
