<h2><span><span class="conr">#6</span> <a href="viewtopic.php?pid=988#p988">2017-04-19 16:19:42</a></span></h2>
<div class="box">
<div class="inbox">
<div class="postbody">
<div class="postleft">
<dl>
<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=8117">umsongb</a></strong></dt>
<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Community Member</strong></dd>
<dd><span>Registered: 2017-04-09</span></dd>
<dd><span>Posts: 25</span></dd>
</dl>
</div>
<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: wrong keyboard and time</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><cite>Newbie wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>I&#039;m new to Linux and Parrot Security OS was the choice for my first Linux distro.</p><p>I can install and boot the OS, but the keyboard and time settings are wrong. </p><p>I&#039;m German, and the notebook is a Lenovo Thinkpad E470 with a German QWERTZ keyboard. <br/>So I choose in the installation Language: German, Location: Germany, and Keyboard Layout: German, <br/>but after installing, the keyboard works as QWERTY and also some symbols are wrong. </p><p>The default time settings are also wrong and I can change them easily in the MATE menu, but after another login the time settings are the same wrong default settings.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>Greetings,</p><p>After my installation yesterday, I noticed my clock was showing different time like u, but after executing the CMDs I suggested earlier a message about UTC popped up.&#160; After some digging, I noticed my system was reporting that UTC time is set and my local time also based on UTC.&#160; From terminal try running &#039;ntp start&#039; then reboot.&#160; </p><p>I don&#039;t know if u have solved this, but seems like I stumbled upon a little shortcut.&#160; From what I understand, the problem ur facing is due to a mixup between system clock and UTC time setup.</p><p>So I ran the following from a terminal and then rebooted.&#160; After logging in, the clock was back to normal</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>utp start</code></pre></div><p>Sorry about earlier suggestions.&#160; Like I said, I&#039;m also a newbie.&#160; Hope u this could help u in anyway. =)</p><p>Peace.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
